July 28, 2017 12:34 PM ET
Electric Utilities

Company Overview of South Carolina Electric & Gas Company



Snapshot People




Company Overview
South Carolina Electric & Gas Company generates, transmits, distributes, and sells electricity primarily in the United States. It generates electricity using nuclear, hydro, solar, biomass, natural gas, and coal. The company’s resale customers consist of municipalities, electric cooperatives, and other investor-owned utilities, as well as registered marketers, and federal and state electric agencies. It serves wholesale and retail customers; and various industries comprising chemicals, educational services, paper products, food products, lumber and wood products, health services, textile manufacturing, rubber and miscellaneous plastic products, automotive and tire, and fabricated metal produ...
South Carolina Electric & Gas Company generates, transmits, distributes, and sells electricity primarily in the United States. It generates electricity using nuclear, hydro, solar, biomass, natural gas, and coal. The company’s resale customers consist of municipalities, electric cooperatives, and other investor-owned utilities, as well as registered marketers, and federal and state electric agencies. It serves wholesale and retail customers; and various industries comprising chemicals, educational services, paper products, food products, lumber and wood products, health services, textile manufacturing, rubber and miscellaneous plastic products, automotive and tire, and fabricated metal products. As of December 31, 2016, the company offered electricity to approximately 709,000 customers; and served approximately 358,000 natural gas customers in South Carolina. It owns 433 substations with an aggregate transformer capacity of 31.5 million Kilovolt ampere; 3,442 miles of transmission system; 18,522 overhead pole miles of distribution system and 7,441 underground trench miles of distribution system; and 17,375 miles of distribution mains and related service facilities. The company was founded in 1923 and is based in Cayce, South Carolina. South Carolina Electric & Gas Company is a subsidiary of SCANA Corporation.
Detailed Description


