South Carolina Electric & Gas Company Key Developments

South Carolina Electric & Gas Company Reports Unaudited Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
Apr 27 17
South Carolina Electric & Gas Company reported unaudited earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported earnings of $112 million, or earnings per share of 78 cents, compared to $116 million, or 81 cents per share, in the same quarter of 2016.


South Carolina Electric & Gas Company Reports Unaudited Earnings Results for the Fourth Quarter and Full Year Ended December 31, 2016
Feb 16 17
South Carolina Electric & Gas Company reported unaudited earnings results for the fourth quarter and full year of December 31, 2016. For the year, the company reported earnings of $526 million or earnings per share of $3.68 compared to $480 million or $3.35 per share in 2015. Abnormal weather increased earnings by 19 cents per share in 2016, compared to 8 cents per share in 2015.  

For the fourth quarter of 2016, the company reported earnings of $93 million or 65 cents per share compared to $75 million or 52 cents per share in the same quarter of 2015.  Abnormal weather decreased earnings by 8 cents per share compared to a decrease of 14 cents per share in the same quarter of 2015.


South Carolina Electric & Gas Company and Westinghouse Electric Company Receive Order from Dispute Resolution Board Regarding the Construction Milestone Payment Schedule
Dec 5 16
South Carolina Electric & Gas Company and Westinghouse Electric Company received an order issued by the Dispute Resolution Board (DRB) on December 2, 2016 regarding the construction milestone payment schedule. The DRB was established under the October 2015 Amendment to the Engineering, Procurement, and Construction agreement (EPC Agreement) with WEC for the two new nuclear units under construction at the V.C. Summer Station in Jenkinsville, South Carolina. The order instructs the parties to use the approved methodology when determining the amounts to be paid for the previously agreed upon milestones for the remainder of construction. The total of all payments under the EPC Agreement remains the amount stated in the fixed price option, which the Public Service Commission of South Carolina authorized SCE&G to exercise in November 2016. SCE&G is evaluating the impact of this decision and will provide updated CAPEX and Financing Plans once the Company has completed its review.


